main event: Two observers watching television in a private home observed two bright objects passing overhead at high speed on December 30, 1959.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 30 minutes,The observers were unsure of the nature of the objects,Additional information was not obtained due to the lack of visual confirmation of the objects,Comments suggest that if the objects had been visualized, more information could have been gathered,The conclusion was that the sighted objects were not unknown and possibly identified as balloon or aircraft.
sighted object: two bright objects in the sky
